    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Flutes with a globular body, made of clay, porcelain, wood, or a natural vessel-shaped object such as a gourd or coconut, in which the air stream is directed against the sharp edge of a round blowhole.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000026541/Marcuse, Musical Instruments Dictionary (1975)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Flautas de cuerpo globular, hechas de arcilla, porcelana, madera o de un objeto natural en forma de vasija, como una calabaza o coco, en las cuales la columna de aire choca contra el borde afilado de una embocadura redonda.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fluiten die een bolle vorm hebben; gemaakt van klei, porselein, hout of bolvormige naturalia zoals een kalebas of kokosnoot, waarin de luchtstroom tegen de scherpe rand van een rond blaasgat wordt geleid. Uitzondering is de ocarina welke in tegenstelling tot andere bolvormige fluiten wèl een aanblaasbuis (duct) heeft.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052452/Encyclopedie van muziekinstrumenten (1977)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>有著一個地球狀的形體的笛子，是由黏土、瓷器、木材，或者是一個自然成形的球狀物件，例如一個葫蘆或者是椰子所製作而成的，在此樂器中，空氣的氣流是朝著一個圓形吹孔的銳利邊緣導向的。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Flöte mit kugelförmigem Körper aus Ton, Porzellan, Holz oder einem natürlichen gefäßförmigen Objekt wie eine Kalebasse oder Kokosnuss, in der der Luftstrom gegen die scharfe Kante eines runden Blasloches gelenkt wird.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
